OL,5, Soaring energy prices which threaten   
OL,6, the living standards of millions could 
OL,7, last up to two years, the boss of the  
OL,8, UK's biggest energy supplier has said. 
OL,10,FChris O'Shea, chief executive of       
OL,11,FBritish Gas owner Centrica, said there 
OL,12,Fwas "no reason" to expect gas prices   
OL,13,Fwould come down "any time soon".       
OL,15,FHe said hopes that bills rising by more
OL,16,Fthan 50% to about #2,000 a year would  
OL,17,Fbe short-lived may be misplaced.       
OL,19,FRising energy bills have raised        
OL,20,Fconcerns over the cost of living.      
